1
00:00:05,671 --> 00:00:07,371
(Child actors were accompanied
by a guardian...)

2
00:00:07,431 --> 00:00:09,101
(and filmed in a safe,
supervised environment.)

3
00:00:10,201 --> 00:00:13,441
- It's about "Human Theater."
- Look, if you're not comfortable,

4
00:00:13,441 --> 00:00:14,871
you don't have to be on the show.

5
00:00:15,271 --> 00:00:16,281
Do it all.

6
00:00:17,381 --> 00:00:18,441
Really?

7
00:00:19,081 --> 00:00:22,021
Yes. Do it all.
A promise is a promise.

8
00:00:23,881 --> 00:00:24,881
But...

9
00:00:25,921 --> 00:00:27,191
from now on,

10
00:00:28,591 --> 00:00:29,791
we're not friends.

11
00:00:30,821 --> 00:00:31,821
What?

12
00:00:47,241 --> 00:00:48,711
How petty and childish.

13
00:00:49,041 --> 00:00:50,911
Breaking off your friendship
like that?

14
00:00:52,381 --> 00:00:55,981
At least, it's a relief
he's still doing "Human Theater."

15
00:00:57,081 --> 00:00:59,791
Stay strong
and just focus on your dream.

16
00:01:00,221 --> 00:01:03,521
Winning that city council seat
is your dream, right?

17
00:01:04,321 --> 00:01:07,161
Should I just go grovel
before Jeong Han's entire family?

18
00:01:07,761 --> 00:01:10,001
If the rest of the family
finds out about this,

19
00:01:10,931 --> 00:01:13,401
I honestly don't think I could stand
the way they'd look at me.

20
00:01:14,601 --> 00:01:15,841
Don't worry.

21
00:01:16,201 --> 00:01:19,741
I met with Gong Ju Ah yesterday
and made it very clear...

22
00:01:19,811 --> 00:01:22,341
that she is not to tell the family
or anyone at work.

23
00:01:23,541 --> 00:01:24,711
Honestly...

24
00:01:25,241 --> 00:01:28,581
I told you not to do anything.
Why did you go and do that?

25
00:01:29,721 --> 00:01:33,521
I was afraid the VP
would be disappointed in us...

26
00:01:33,921 --> 00:01:36,391
if she found out
we staged the whole thing.

27
00:01:56,941 --> 00:01:58,611
Sorry, I haven't been in touch.

28
00:01:59,251 --> 00:02:02,121
I didn't want you to worry
if I said I was sick.

29
00:02:03,081 --> 00:02:04,421
I was worried.

30
00:02:05,491 --> 00:02:06,821
I thought you were leaving.

31
00:02:07,151 --> 00:02:08,761
Where would I go?

32
00:02:09,521 --> 00:02:12,661
You asked if it would've been better
if you had never returned.

33
00:02:13,831 --> 00:02:14,831
So...

34
00:02:15,261 --> 00:02:18,771
I thought you got scouted
and were leaving for Spain.

35
00:02:19,101 --> 00:02:20,731
There's no way.

36
00:02:22,031 --> 00:02:25,201
When I said I regretted
meeting you again...

37
00:02:26,171 --> 00:02:27,641
I didn't mean any of it.

38
00:02:29,411 --> 00:02:30,711
I only said it because I was angry.

39
00:02:32,311 --> 00:02:33,311
I know.

40
00:02:40,991 --> 00:02:42,291
To be honest,

41
00:02:43,521 --> 00:02:45,591
I can't live without you now.

42
00:02:46,631 --> 00:02:47,891
My first love,

43
00:02:48,561 --> 00:02:50,401
my savior, Gong Ju Ah,

44
00:02:51,831 --> 00:02:54,331
you're here with me every day,

45
00:02:54,771 --> 00:02:58,641
caring for me and worrying about me.

46
00:02:59,541 --> 00:03:01,541
How could I possibly leave?

47
00:03:13,451 --> 00:03:16,421
He ended their friendship?
Dad must be furious.

48
00:03:16,891 --> 00:03:20,361
Tell me about it.
This is giving me such a headache.

49
00:03:20,631 --> 00:03:22,901
- Why the headache, Uncle?
- Me?

50
00:03:23,201 --> 00:03:24,731
What? Oh, it's nothing.

51
00:03:25,101 --> 00:03:27,131
I'm running late.
I have to eat fast and get to work.

52
00:03:27,771 --> 00:03:29,971
- But it's Saturday.
- Right. It is Saturday.

53
00:03:33,211 --> 00:03:35,071
Hey, are you guys having breakfast?

54
00:03:35,741 --> 00:03:36,741
Yes.

55
00:03:37,081 --> 00:03:38,581
What about my brother?
Is he still asleep?

56
00:03:40,011 --> 00:03:42,981
Dae Han.
Did something happen with him?

57
00:03:43,751 --> 00:03:45,621
No, everything's fine.

58
00:03:46,291 --> 00:03:47,821
Here you go, Seong Mi.
Your soy milk.

59
00:03:50,321 --> 00:03:53,161
But I can't eat if I want my photos
to turn out well today.

60
00:03:53,231 --> 00:03:56,201
Come on. You can't shoot all day
on an empty stomach.

61
00:03:56,531 --> 00:03:57,601
Drink it all up.

62
00:03:58,161 --> 00:03:59,171
Okay.

63
00:03:59,931 --> 00:04:02,401
Why isn't Ju Ah down yet?
We need to go.

64
00:04:02,771 --> 00:04:04,471
- She's not in her room.
- What?

65
00:04:04,541 --> 00:04:05,541
Maybe she left early?

66
00:04:05,741 --> 00:04:08,071
What are you talking about?
We were supposed to go together.

67
00:04:08,941 --> 00:04:10,011
Wait a minute.

68
00:04:10,341 --> 00:04:12,451
Did anyone see Ju Ah
come home last night?

69
00:04:17,721 --> 00:04:18,921
- Wait a second.
- What?

70
00:04:19,051 --> 00:04:20,051
What's going on?

71
00:04:20,551 --> 00:04:21,551
Oh, dear.

72
00:04:25,091 --> 00:04:27,561
She's not picking up?
Let me try calling.

73
00:04:28,591 --> 00:04:29,631
What's going on?

74
00:04:30,031 --> 00:04:32,531
What's gotten into her?
She didn't even call us.

75
00:04:32,731 --> 00:04:35,671
Hey, Mom, don't worry too much.
She's probably at the office.

76
00:04:36,401 --> 00:04:37,771
Hey, Ju Ah.

77
00:04:38,741 --> 00:04:39,771
Where are you?

78
00:04:40,671 --> 00:04:42,681
- Grandma?
- Give me the phone.

79
00:04:43,541 --> 00:04:45,881
Hey, Gong Ju Ah!
Where are you right now?

80
00:04:48,811 --> 00:04:50,921
Oh, well...

81
00:04:51,181 --> 00:04:52,591
Hey, you...

82
00:04:52,851 --> 00:04:54,521
Did you just stay out all night
without saying a word?

83
00:04:54,921 --> 00:04:56,421
Hey, where are you right now?

84
00:04:57,921 --> 00:04:59,591
- Well...
- Babe.

85
00:05:01,791 --> 00:05:03,931
What? "Babe?"

86
00:05:05,201 --> 00:05:07,371
Don't tell me you're with a man!

87
00:05:08,101 --> 00:05:09,101
A man?

88
00:05:09,871 --> 00:05:10,871
A man?

89
00:05:11,641 --> 00:05:13,571
All of you, knock it off.

90
00:05:14,041 --> 00:05:16,581
She can do what she wants.
She's old enough.

91
00:05:16,681 --> 00:05:17,711
Mom!

92
00:05:17,841 --> 00:05:19,781
What are you talking about?
Ju Ah isn't even married yet.

93
00:05:20,311 --> 00:05:21,911
Hey, you punk!

94
00:05:22,351 --> 00:05:26,091
Who are you? What right do you have
to call our Ju Ah "babe?"

95
00:05:26,391 --> 00:05:27,521
Who are you? You punk!

96
00:05:28,521 --> 00:05:31,321
That was... I think
the person next to me said that.

97
00:05:31,791 --> 00:05:33,661
I'm in an elevator.
You're breaking up.

98
00:05:42,641 --> 00:05:43,971
What the...

99
00:05:44,971 --> 00:05:47,041
- I can't believe her.
- My goodness.

100
00:05:47,341 --> 00:05:48,341
Did she hang up?

101
00:05:48,411 --> 00:05:51,341
The nerve, calling our Ju Ah "babe"
without my permission.

102
00:05:51,881 --> 00:05:53,281
Exactly.

103
00:05:54,211 --> 00:05:56,251
I swear, that girl is not
getting away with this.

104
00:05:56,721 --> 00:05:59,191
Come on, get going.
You'll be late for your shoot.

105
00:05:59,821 --> 00:06:00,891
Hurry.

106
00:06:04,221 --> 00:06:05,261
Here.

107
00:06:05,731 --> 00:06:07,591
You think they bought it?

108
00:06:08,531 --> 00:06:09,561
Hard to say.

109
00:06:11,101 --> 00:06:12,771
Seriously, what are we going to do?

110
00:06:14,031 --> 00:06:15,031
By the way.

111
00:06:15,701 --> 00:06:17,101
Why did you sleep here?

112
00:06:17,441 --> 00:06:19,811
What are you talking about?
You asked me to stay with you.

113
00:06:20,241 --> 00:06:23,011
Yes, but I didn't think
you'd stay all night.

114
00:06:25,041 --> 00:06:26,151
Unbelievable.

115
00:06:27,481 --> 00:06:30,421
This is so unfair. My family
will completely misunderstand.

116
00:06:30,481 --> 00:06:32,351
I wouldn't feel so wronged
if we'd actually done something.

117
00:06:32,551 --> 00:06:35,321
We could do something now
so you don't feel so wronged.

118
00:06:35,651 --> 00:06:36,821
Gosh, seriously...

119
00:06:44,101 --> 00:06:45,261
My dream came true.

120
00:06:45,631 --> 00:06:47,401
Being like this makes me feel
like we're newlyweds.

121
00:06:48,831 --> 00:06:51,141
How can you say that
at a time like this?

122
00:06:52,741 --> 00:06:56,281
Look, babe. Dr. Han is coming today.

123
00:06:56,511 --> 00:06:58,711
Let's take this chance to be honest
and get their blessing.

124
00:06:58,911 --> 00:07:00,081
Absolutely not.

125
00:07:00,751 --> 00:07:02,681
Our dads aren't even
on speaking terms.

126
00:07:03,251 --> 00:07:06,991
Still, I don't feel right about
deceiving our parents like this.

127
00:07:07,151 --> 00:07:10,561
It's all about timing. And now is
definitely not the right time.

128
00:07:10,761 --> 00:07:12,321
But I want to tell them.

129
00:07:20,271 --> 00:07:23,571
Real classy.
Staying out all night with a guy.

130
00:07:24,401 --> 00:07:25,641
Is Mom furious?

131
00:07:26,411 --> 00:07:29,811
Do you even have to ask?
Who are you with, anyway?

132
00:07:31,881 --> 00:07:33,711
Don't tell me you're with Hyun Bin.

133
00:07:35,711 --> 00:07:36,881
Of course not.

134
00:07:37,421 --> 00:07:40,551
- Are you sure?
- Positive. I worked all night.

135
00:07:40,621 --> 00:07:42,321
And now, I'm on my way to the shoot.

136
00:07:42,491 --> 00:07:46,731
Anyway, he's totally off-limits.
You know Dad...

137
00:07:46,791 --> 00:07:49,831
is a wreck because of that stunt
his parents pulled, right?

138
00:07:50,201 --> 00:07:53,831
Hey, do not tell Grandma or Mom
about this. Got it?

139
00:07:57,301 --> 00:07:58,741
Woo Jae knows too?

140
00:07:59,911 --> 00:08:02,141
Yes. And so does Uncle.

141
00:08:17,861 --> 00:08:20,561
Father, we're going to go
check on the store.

142
00:08:20,631 --> 00:08:22,601
All right. Go have a look.

143
00:08:22,931 --> 00:08:26,231
Se Ri,
Min Seo agreed to tutor Ji Hu.

144
00:08:26,371 --> 00:08:28,031
Really? That's great.

145
00:08:28,231 --> 00:08:31,301
Doesn't that mean
you need to hire a new part-timer?

146
00:08:31,401 --> 00:08:33,711
Oh, I've already hired someone.

147
00:08:34,071 --> 00:08:37,341
Min Seo is moving into my room
tomorrow night!

148
00:08:37,881 --> 00:08:40,611
- Won't that be awkward?
- It's only for a few months.

149
00:08:40,681 --> 00:08:42,181
I think it'll be fun.
I like the idea.

150
00:08:42,381 --> 00:08:45,921
Gosh, you sound like you just found
your long-lost sister.

151
00:08:46,191 --> 00:08:47,691
Tell me about it.

152
00:08:47,851 --> 00:08:51,691
Grandpa, Dad. I got a part-time job.

153
00:08:51,821 --> 00:08:52,931
My gosh, really?

154
00:08:53,691 --> 00:08:58,101
Father! Honey!
Eun Bin got a part-time job.

155
00:08:58,231 --> 00:08:59,931
You did? What kind of job?

156
00:09:01,471 --> 00:09:05,841
- A bookstore. I'll work there.
- Good for you.

157
00:09:06,211 --> 00:09:09,141
I'm glad you're acting responsibly.
If you're doing it, do it well.

158
00:09:09,211 --> 00:09:11,141
I will. And if I work really hard,

159
00:09:11,211 --> 00:09:13,881
- you'll help me. Right, Grandpa?
- All right. We'll see how you do.

160
00:09:13,911 --> 00:09:15,411
Yes!

161
00:09:27,031 --> 00:09:29,261
What is it?
Want me to bring you a snack?

162
00:09:29,831 --> 00:09:32,001
Mom, about Mr. Gong at the clinic...

163
00:09:32,161 --> 00:09:35,301
Gosh, why do you keep bringing up
Mr. Gong?

164
00:09:36,771 --> 00:09:38,441
Something's been bothering me
a little.

165
00:09:39,441 --> 00:09:40,441
What?

166
00:09:47,781 --> 00:09:50,721
What's wrong?
Something's up with you, right?

167
00:09:54,491 --> 00:09:56,461
No, nothing's wrong.

168
00:09:58,891 --> 00:10:01,331
Oh, it's Seung Cheol.

169
00:10:03,531 --> 00:10:05,061
Hello? Yes.

170
00:10:07,501 --> 00:10:10,171
I'm going to my room
to get some rest.

171
00:10:19,211 --> 00:10:22,311
You said you needed time to think.
Have you made up your mind already?

172
00:10:24,081 --> 00:10:25,721
Okay.
You want to meet and talk in person?

173
00:10:26,391 --> 00:10:28,751
Sounds good. Yes, okay. All right.

174
00:10:29,921 --> 00:10:31,921
I really miss you.

175
00:10:32,761 --> 00:10:33,931
My dear Dong Suk.

176
00:10:42,771 --> 00:10:43,871
(Dr. Han Seong Mi
Photoshoot Proposal)

177
00:10:51,311 --> 00:10:54,581
What?
Why are you looking at me like that?

178
00:10:54,911 --> 00:10:57,751
You were wearing that same outfit
yesterday.

179
00:11:01,821 --> 00:11:04,461
No, I wasn't.
Something's wrong with your eyes.

180
00:11:05,161 --> 00:11:06,931
How dare you question my keen eye
for detail?

181
00:11:08,961 --> 00:11:11,631
- What about Dr. Han?
- Yes. She's on her way.

182
00:11:11,961 --> 00:11:14,171
By the way, Director,
are you feeling any better?

183
00:11:14,331 --> 00:11:17,371
I took medicine and slept soundly.
I feel perfectly fine now.

184
00:11:17,441 --> 00:11:22,011
Gosh, I had no idea you were sick.
I feared you'd been poached.

185
00:11:22,071 --> 00:11:23,741
Come on, that would never happen.

186
00:11:23,981 --> 00:11:26,411
Right? I'll go check
the models' hair and makeup.

187
00:11:26,411 --> 00:11:28,111
- I'll be right back.
- Okay, let's go.

188
00:11:32,051 --> 00:11:33,851
You're here, Dr. Han.

189
00:11:36,061 --> 00:11:39,931
We still have some time, don't we?
Can I speak with them for a moment?

190
00:11:40,231 --> 00:11:41,361
Yes, of course.

191
00:11:44,731 --> 00:11:46,431
I am so busted.

192
00:11:47,901 --> 00:11:48,901
Dr. Han!

193
00:11:51,901 --> 00:11:53,571
- Mom.
- Dr. Han?

194
00:11:53,671 --> 00:11:56,941
How could you?
I'm so disappointed in you.

195
00:11:57,211 --> 00:11:59,751
Mom, what in the world is wrong?
Talk to me.

196
00:12:00,051 --> 00:12:01,181
Hey, what's going on?

197
00:12:01,181 --> 00:12:04,151
- Did I make a mistake or something?
- What? A mistake?

198
00:12:04,981 --> 00:12:07,391
- I was wrong.
- You certainly were.

199
00:12:07,891 --> 00:12:10,591
Even if you're adults and dating,
that's no excuse.

200
00:12:10,891 --> 00:12:13,531
You know
Ju Ah lives with her family.

201
00:12:13,731 --> 00:12:15,431
And yet, without permission...

202
00:12:15,491 --> 00:12:16,901
How dare you let her stay out
all night?

203
00:12:17,361 --> 00:12:21,271
- I... I did?
- Mom, no! It's not what you think!

204
00:12:21,871 --> 00:12:23,171
What do you mean
it's not what I think?

205
00:12:23,401 --> 00:12:26,871
Dr. Han, it's time for your fitting.

206
00:12:41,491 --> 00:12:42,491
So, let me get this straight.

207
00:12:43,321 --> 00:12:47,831
It wasn't enough that you two were
dating secretly behind my back,

208
00:12:48,031 --> 00:12:50,031
but you also used me as a cover
without me even knowing?

209
00:12:50,531 --> 00:12:51,631
I'm sorry, Jun Hyeok.

210
00:12:52,871 --> 00:12:55,531
Seriously?
You should've at least told me!

211
00:12:55,601 --> 00:12:59,041
You let me get chewed out
without knowing why. It still hurts.

212
00:12:59,141 --> 00:13:02,781
I'm sorry you had to
take the fall for me, Mr. Park.

213
00:13:03,741 --> 00:13:05,581
I'm really disappointed in you,
Director.

214
00:13:05,741 --> 00:13:08,751
No, it's just...
If the VP found out about us,

215
00:13:09,151 --> 00:13:12,281
I was afraid she'd cause trouble,
so we hid it.

216
00:13:12,651 --> 00:13:16,321
It was my idea to keep it secret.
I didn't want our coworkers to know.

217
00:13:17,921 --> 00:13:22,861
Fine, I get hiding it until now.
But aren't your families reconciled?

218
00:13:23,001 --> 00:13:25,031
They've been going back and forth.

219
00:13:25,031 --> 00:13:27,471
We're waiting
for the right moment to tell them.

220
00:13:27,731 --> 00:13:30,601
So you expect me
to just be your shield until then?

221
00:13:30,671 --> 00:13:33,771
No. I'll make it clear that
there's nothing between us.

222
00:13:34,171 --> 00:13:38,611
Oh, and the VP must not find out.
Everything must be kept secret.

223
00:13:39,451 --> 00:13:42,781
- Are you ordering me right now?
- Hey, now...

224
00:13:43,821 --> 00:13:46,791
A request. I'm asking you.

225
00:13:46,851 --> 00:13:49,861
Please, Jun Hyeok.
Don't tell the VP.

226
00:13:51,661 --> 00:13:55,231
Gosh, fine. I'll keep my promise.

227
00:13:58,461 --> 00:14:01,601
All right, here we go.
I need lots of energy, please.

228
00:14:01,671 --> 00:14:03,471
Here we go. One, two, three!

229
00:14:05,271 --> 00:14:07,711
That's great. Just like that.

230
00:14:08,241 --> 00:14:09,241
Okay.

231
00:14:09,911 --> 00:14:12,041
She's so beautiful.

232
00:14:13,381 --> 00:14:14,781
Great. Can I get a bigger smile?

233
00:14:20,791 --> 00:14:21,921
Yes, Vice President.

234
00:14:22,321 --> 00:14:25,991
That's right. He took the day off
yesterday because of a cold.

235
00:14:26,561 --> 00:14:31,101
Yes, and Cartio's offer seems
to have been a false alarm.

236
00:14:31,501 --> 00:14:33,101
But, Vice President...

237
00:14:33,701 --> 00:14:36,101
Something really interesting
has come up.

238
00:14:37,741 --> 00:14:41,611
I'm in the middle of the shoot,
so I'll call you back.

239
00:14:42,071 --> 00:14:43,081
Okay.

240
00:14:47,081 --> 00:14:51,021
Just as I thought.
"I'll keep my promise?"

241
00:14:51,451 --> 00:14:54,751
No, wait.
Director, it's just that...

242
00:14:54,851 --> 00:14:59,531
The VP has it rough on weekends,
taking care of the Chairman,

243
00:14:59,591 --> 00:15:02,691
and she doesn't really have much
to look forward to.

244
00:15:02,861 --> 00:15:05,331
I'll tell her myself
when things become official.

245
00:15:05,331 --> 00:15:07,131
Don't say a word.

246
00:15:07,831 --> 00:15:10,141
If you keep this up,
I might just have to tell Dr. Han...

247
00:15:10,641 --> 00:15:12,401
that you two are dating.

248
00:15:12,401 --> 00:15:15,541
Fine. Be my guest.
That's what I was hoping for anyway.

249
00:15:21,651 --> 00:15:22,651
A little more...

250
00:15:22,711 --> 00:15:25,681
All right, let's take a break.
Then we'll do Dr. Han's solos.

251
00:15:30,491 --> 00:15:32,521
- This is it, right?
- Give it here.

252
00:15:35,931 --> 00:15:37,831
Mr. Park, are you free tomorrow?

253
00:15:38,661 --> 00:15:41,601
I don't have anything scheduled
for tomorrow.

254
00:15:42,901 --> 00:15:46,241
Then come over to our house
for lunch tomorrow.

255
00:15:47,171 --> 00:15:48,171
Excuse me?

256
00:15:49,471 --> 00:15:52,311
What are you doing?
What is this all of a sudden?

257
00:15:52,411 --> 00:15:54,651
It's not like we're getting married.
This is so awkward.

258
00:15:54,781 --> 00:15:57,481
So you slept over
with no intention of marrying him?

259
00:15:58,221 --> 00:16:01,591
That's rich, coming from the woman
who had a shotgun wedding.

260
00:16:01,891 --> 00:16:03,591
I'm worried you'll make
the same mistake I did...

261
00:16:03,591 --> 00:16:05,561
and regret it later. How about that?

262
00:16:06,791 --> 00:16:08,961
Come and meet the family,

263
00:16:09,061 --> 00:16:11,831
and formally ask for our permission
to date Ju Ah.

264
00:16:12,031 --> 00:16:16,371
- Oh, the thing is...
- The thing is, Jun Hyeok...

265
00:16:16,671 --> 00:16:19,941
- What?
- Jun Hyeok isn't my boyfriend...

266
00:16:23,141 --> 00:16:25,441
My boyfriend is...

267
00:16:31,651 --> 00:16:33,451
So, what's on the menu
for lunch tomorrow?

268
00:16:34,291 --> 00:16:36,991
What are you in the mood for?
Just say the word.

269
00:16:37,821 --> 00:16:41,891
- I'll eat anything, really.
- Hey, what are you doing?

270
00:16:42,431 --> 00:16:46,061
Her grandma is dying to meet you,
so don't feel pressured. Just come.

271
00:16:46,601 --> 00:16:50,601
- You can have a drink with her dad.
- I'd love that.

272
00:16:52,301 --> 00:16:54,471
I'm sorry I hit you earlier.

273
00:16:55,211 --> 00:16:57,981
I don't know what came over me.
You just felt like family.

274
00:16:58,041 --> 00:17:01,311
Please, hit me again.
I don't have any family,

275
00:17:01,381 --> 00:17:03,921
so when you treat me like that,
it actually feels nice.

276
00:17:14,361 --> 00:17:18,431
Wow, you're a natural.
Oh, my. That smile!

277
00:17:18,501 --> 00:17:20,071
So beautiful.

278
00:17:22,001 --> 00:17:23,841
What exactly is your game here?

279
00:17:25,141 --> 00:17:28,711
What? I'm trying to help you two
out of the goodness of my heart,

280
00:17:28,771 --> 00:17:31,011
and you think
I have some ulterior motive?

281
00:17:31,341 --> 00:17:32,441
I'll be...

282
00:17:33,481 --> 00:17:37,021
a reliable shield for you two
until you're ready to tell everyone.

283
00:17:37,221 --> 00:17:39,151
When the truth comes out,

284
00:17:39,151 --> 00:17:41,121
I don't want Dr. Han
to hold it against me,

285
00:17:41,251 --> 00:17:42,751
so you'll have to
explain this to her.

286
00:17:44,391 --> 00:17:46,831
Just say it. What are your terms?

287
00:17:47,991 --> 00:17:50,231
Terms? You have terms?

288
00:17:51,831 --> 00:17:53,071
What are your terms?

289
00:17:53,501 --> 00:17:55,201
Just tell me.
I'll do anything you ask.

290
00:17:55,771 --> 00:17:59,101
Once our brothers make up
and we get our families' blessing,

291
00:17:59,771 --> 00:18:00,911
I'll date you then.

292
00:18:03,081 --> 00:18:05,441
Hey, that's a given.
Of course, that'll happen.

293
00:18:06,481 --> 00:18:08,681
Why do you like me so much, anyway?

294
00:18:09,981 --> 00:18:10,981
You really want to know?

295
00:18:13,521 --> 00:18:14,551
Hold on.

296
00:18:15,751 --> 00:18:16,891
Well...

297
00:18:19,761 --> 00:18:22,061
You're the endorphin
that makes me smile,

298
00:18:23,601 --> 00:18:26,831
the dopamine
that makes my heart race,

299
00:18:27,931 --> 00:18:30,941
the vitamin that picks me up
when I'm exhausted,

300
00:18:31,941 --> 00:18:34,541
and the catalyst
that makes me a better person.

301
00:18:35,511 --> 00:18:36,711
Yang Dong Suk, you...

302
00:18:37,841 --> 00:18:39,241
You're the one thing
my life absolutely needs.

303
00:18:40,851 --> 00:18:42,111
You're my prescription for love.

304
00:18:47,821 --> 00:18:49,121
Maybe we should just...

305
00:18:50,691 --> 00:18:52,061
date in secret?

306
00:18:54,431 --> 00:18:55,431
What? Why?

307
00:18:56,091 --> 00:18:58,161
Ji Hu was saying that...

308
00:18:58,231 --> 00:19:01,931
if my mom and your dad
live together as a married couple,

309
00:19:02,031 --> 00:19:05,041
then we might not be legally allowed
to be together.

310
00:19:05,771 --> 00:19:06,941
Is that true?

311
00:19:07,471 --> 00:19:08,541
I don't think that's true.

312
00:19:08,841 --> 00:19:10,941
Even if it's not,
it's still weird, you know.

313
00:19:11,711 --> 00:19:13,751
Can you imagine
how much the neighbors will gossip?

314
00:19:14,351 --> 00:19:17,251
Then we can just move
to a different neighborhood.

315
00:19:18,151 --> 00:19:22,151
- I'm just not comfortable with it.
- Not comfortable? What's wrong?

316
00:19:23,221 --> 00:19:24,661
I'm going to marry you,
no matter what.

317
00:19:25,061 --> 00:19:27,761
Are you crazy? What are you saying,
marriage? Forget it.

318
00:19:27,831 --> 00:19:28,891
What do you mean, "forget it?"

319
00:19:29,631 --> 00:19:30,901
You slept with me.

320
00:19:31,161 --> 00:19:33,231
Gosh, you're insane.
Who slept with whom?

321
00:19:33,301 --> 00:19:36,101
So we didn't?
We went to a motel and slept.

322
00:19:36,641 --> 00:19:38,271
Be quiet! No, we didn't!

323
00:19:38,341 --> 00:19:41,111
What do you mean, no?
Sleeping together means we marry.

324
00:19:41,171 --> 00:19:43,181
- Gosh, seriously!
- I'm marrying you, no matter what.

325
00:19:43,381 --> 00:19:44,481
Why are you being like this?

326
00:19:44,481 --> 00:19:46,711
- I'll absolutely marry you! I must!
- Hey, seriously!

327
00:19:46,781 --> 00:19:48,581
- Hey, stop!
- Be quiet!

328
00:19:49,181 --> 00:19:51,781
That's right.
You sleep together, you get married.

329
00:19:54,551 --> 00:19:58,191
Vice President,
we didn't exactly sleep together...

330
00:19:58,621 --> 00:20:02,061
That was... I had a really bad cold,
and she was just looking after me...

331
00:20:02,731 --> 00:20:04,931
But do we really have to
justify ourselves like this?

332
00:20:05,001 --> 00:20:08,401
Shut it, Pacu Nacho!
As if lying to me wasn't enough,

333
00:20:08,471 --> 00:20:10,671
and to think I was sick with worry
that you might leave,

334
00:20:10,941 --> 00:20:13,211
- I just want to smack you one.
- Unbelievable.

335
00:20:13,271 --> 00:20:15,311
Vice President, please.

336
00:20:15,541 --> 00:20:18,381
I don't want this getting out
at the office.

337
00:20:18,681 --> 00:20:19,711
All right.

338
00:20:20,151 --> 00:20:23,181
- But you'll report to me instead.
- Vice President!

339
00:20:23,251 --> 00:20:24,681
If you don't like it, then...
Mr. Park.

340
00:20:25,081 --> 00:20:27,351
Go over to Ms. Gong's house tomorrow
and tell her family.

341
00:20:27,621 --> 00:20:29,921
Tell them her boyfriend isn't you,
it's Yang Hyun Bin.

342
00:20:30,321 --> 00:20:32,121
Yes, I understand, Vice President.

343
00:20:34,631 --> 00:20:37,931
And Pacu Nacho, we'll switch you
to a long-term contract.

344
00:20:40,231 --> 00:20:41,331
You want that too,
don't you, Ms. Gong?

345
00:20:42,031 --> 00:20:43,031
Vice President.

346
00:20:43,341 --> 00:20:46,241
I don't want to hold
Director Yang back.

347
00:20:46,541 --> 00:20:49,511
He has global opportunities,
but he'd be tied to just us.

348
00:20:49,571 --> 00:20:50,981
Let's do it. The long-term contract.

349
00:20:53,281 --> 00:20:58,021
This might be a tactical retreat,
but I'll still pursue Ms. Gong,

350
00:20:58,251 --> 00:21:00,591
so this is for the best,
to put everyone's mind at ease.

351
00:21:01,721 --> 00:21:04,461
All right,
what should my role in all this be?

352
00:21:04,761 --> 00:21:06,831
Nothing. Please don't do anything.

353
00:21:07,131 --> 00:21:11,261
- Why not?
- Director Yang's parents...

354
00:21:11,331 --> 00:21:15,331
- see you as a good match for him.
- Still?

355
00:21:15,931 --> 00:21:17,871
I thought I made it clear to them
that wasn't the case.

356
00:21:18,471 --> 00:21:19,471
Okay, that settles it.

357
00:21:19,771 --> 00:21:21,671
I'll go see them myself
and clear up this misunderstanding.

358
00:21:21,741 --> 00:21:26,241
No, I'll take care of it,
so just stay out of it, all right?

359
00:21:26,311 --> 00:21:28,881
Why not?
Then what am I supposed to do?

360
00:21:29,921 --> 00:21:30,921
Vice President?

361
00:21:31,221 --> 00:21:33,751
How about expanding and revamping...

362
00:21:33,751 --> 00:21:35,851
the company's benefits
for married couples?

363
00:21:36,551 --> 00:21:37,821
That's an excellent idea.

364
00:21:38,421 --> 00:21:40,661
It's so much fun
watching the office romances unfold.

365
00:21:40,731 --> 00:21:43,901
Yes. Let's create some clubs
so more people can meet and date.

366
00:21:44,031 --> 00:21:48,531
I want them to date, fight,
get back together, and get married.

367
00:21:49,171 --> 00:21:52,271
You can enjoy
your own real-life dating show.

368
00:21:52,971 --> 00:21:54,041
I love it.

369
00:22:00,351 --> 00:22:03,351
- Hold on. I'll go get the car.
- Wait.

370
00:22:06,351 --> 00:22:08,291
I'm fine. My fever's gone.

371
00:22:10,091 --> 00:22:12,661
But you seem upset, babe.

372
00:22:14,231 --> 00:22:15,691
I'm not exactly thrilled.

373
00:22:16,701 --> 00:22:20,471
I can't believe you got someone else
to act as your boyfriend.

374
00:22:23,231 --> 00:22:25,771
My uncle, Woo Jae, and I...

375
00:22:25,841 --> 00:22:28,271
decided to do whatever we can
to calm my dad down.

376
00:22:28,671 --> 00:22:31,611
As for me,
I'm going to my parents' tomorrow.

377
00:22:31,681 --> 00:22:35,181
I'm going to tell my stepmom to stop
setting me up with the VP.

378
00:22:36,481 --> 00:22:38,081
Did you find the talisman?

379
00:22:38,481 --> 00:22:39,481
Yes.

380
00:22:40,091 --> 00:22:44,161
Honestly, I'm a bit disappointed
in my stepmom after this.

381
00:22:49,591 --> 00:22:50,631
(3H Acupressure Bed)

382
00:22:50,631 --> 00:22:54,731
You take great care of this place.
It's so clean and nice here.

383
00:22:55,101 --> 00:22:58,041
Once you get the hang of it,
it's pretty low-maintenance.

384
00:22:59,001 --> 00:23:01,171
- Did you run this all by yourself?
- I did.

385
00:23:01,641 --> 00:23:03,541
The customer traffic is pretty good,

386
00:23:03,881 --> 00:23:06,681
so if I wasn't emigrating,
I would've kept running it.

387
00:23:07,611 --> 00:23:08,611
I see.

388
00:23:09,711 --> 00:23:10,721
Honey.

389
00:23:11,621 --> 00:23:12,621
What do you think?

390
00:23:12,851 --> 00:23:13,851
Oh, well...

391
00:23:14,351 --> 00:23:15,591
It's nice.

392
00:23:20,361 --> 00:23:23,601
You are? Okay, Hyun Bin. All right.

393
00:23:26,601 --> 00:23:29,171
Honey, Hyun Bin's coming home
for lunch tomorrow.

394
00:23:32,241 --> 00:23:34,371
Why? Are you craving dumplings?

395
00:23:35,441 --> 00:23:36,441
No.

396
00:23:37,181 --> 00:23:39,081
It's just that
Jeong Han loves kimchi dumplings.

397
00:23:39,841 --> 00:23:40,851
Should I get some for him?

398
00:23:41,211 --> 00:23:42,211
What?

399
00:23:43,211 --> 00:23:44,881
I should ask Jeong Han
if he wants some.

400
00:23:44,951 --> 00:23:46,121
No, honey!

401
00:23:46,451 --> 00:23:50,721
Honey. You and Jeong Han
aren't on speaking terms anymore.

402
00:23:50,821 --> 00:23:53,561
That's not true.
That can't be. Not Jeong Han.

403
00:23:53,991 --> 00:23:56,161
He's just pouting a little,
right, honey?

404
00:23:56,861 --> 00:23:57,861
Of course.

405
00:23:58,561 --> 00:24:02,771
He's cold, but once filming starts,
it'll all blow over.

406
00:24:09,841 --> 00:24:11,081
(Sunny Korean Medicine Clinic)

407
00:24:11,181 --> 00:24:12,881
(Gong Myeong Jeong Dae Han Clinic)

408
00:24:15,951 --> 00:24:18,481
Hey, what do you think you're doing?
Seriously.

409
00:24:20,591 --> 00:24:22,251
- Hey!
- Gosh, it's cold.

410
00:24:32,261 --> 00:24:34,431
(Gong Myeong Jeong Dae Han Clinic)

411
00:24:43,611 --> 00:24:47,081
You were so close with Yang Dong Ik.
Why so quiet all of a sudden?

412
00:24:48,911 --> 00:24:52,581
You need energy to have fun.
I must be getting old.

413
00:24:53,891 --> 00:24:56,321
You have a point.
You are getting old.

414
00:24:56,621 --> 00:24:58,091
Your complexion
is looking dull, too.

415
00:24:59,691 --> 00:25:02,761
You have a TV appearance coming up.
Want to get some facials?

416
00:25:03,391 --> 00:25:06,701
It's okay. I know an acupressure tip
that improves your complexion.

417
00:25:07,131 --> 00:25:10,371
- You do?
- Yes. Here, under the cheekbone...

418
00:25:10,571 --> 00:25:13,811
This is the Gwanryohyeol point.
If you press down here gently,

419
00:25:13,871 --> 00:25:17,281
it helps with your circulation
and improves your complexion.

420
00:25:17,711 --> 00:25:19,581
- Really? Right here?
- Yes.

421
00:25:23,551 --> 00:25:25,681
Why are you smiling all of a sudden?
It's creepy.

422
00:25:28,151 --> 00:25:31,861
You know the five stages of grief,
right?

423
00:25:32,261 --> 00:25:34,091
Elisabeth Kubler-Ross?

424
00:25:34,331 --> 00:25:37,231
Yes, that's the one.
What's the order again?

425
00:25:37,601 --> 00:25:40,701
Denial, anger, bargaining,
depression, and acceptance.

426
00:25:42,901 --> 00:25:45,301
Then I must be past the anger stage,

427
00:25:46,001 --> 00:25:48,211
which means I'm in depression
and acceptance.

428
00:25:49,511 --> 00:25:52,041
You're sure nothing's wrong, right?

429
00:25:52,741 --> 00:25:55,111
Yes, nothing's wrong.
What could be wrong?

430
00:25:57,151 --> 00:26:00,151
Right. Ju Ah's boyfriend is coming
for lunch tomorrow.

431
00:26:00,751 --> 00:26:03,891
Yes, I heard.
I guess we'll have a drink.

432
00:26:04,361 --> 00:26:06,961
Man, I'm tired.
I'm going to bed first.

433
00:26:20,811 --> 00:26:22,741
- Oh, Mom.
- Hey.

434
00:26:22,741 --> 00:26:26,441
- Why are you out here?
- I was waiting for Ju Ah.

435
00:26:26,811 --> 00:26:28,251
That kid's not back yet?

436
00:26:29,211 --> 00:26:33,081
Just wait until she gets here.
I'm going to give her an earful.

437
00:26:33,521 --> 00:26:35,551
I'll handle it.
You should go inside.

438
00:26:41,091 --> 00:26:42,091
Mom.

439
00:26:42,591 --> 00:26:43,601
Yes?

440
00:26:44,131 --> 00:26:45,831
Back when I got divorced...

441
00:26:46,561 --> 00:26:47,571
Yes.

442
00:26:48,231 --> 00:26:51,901
You said you regretted
not ending things properly with Dad.

443
00:26:53,341 --> 00:26:54,941
I did.

444
00:26:55,571 --> 00:26:58,341
So, what if... This is
just a hypothetical question.

445
00:26:58,411 --> 00:27:02,111
This is a total hypothetical.
Let's say you met Dad again...

446
00:27:03,081 --> 00:27:05,521
- Then would you divorce him?
- What?

447
00:27:05,721 --> 00:27:09,191
If Dad divorced you
and remarried that other woman,

448
00:27:09,451 --> 00:27:12,091
what would the kids' legal status be
in both families?

449
00:27:12,161 --> 00:27:13,161
I was just curious...

450
00:27:14,191 --> 00:27:15,961
Where is this coming from
all of a sudden?

451
00:27:17,431 --> 00:27:19,001
That's totally out of the blue,
isn't it?

452
00:27:20,901 --> 00:27:22,501
I'm heading in, Mom.

453
00:27:23,531 --> 00:27:27,271
- Good grief. What a crazy kid.
- Seriously.

454
00:27:29,611 --> 00:27:35,081
Can step-siblings get married?

455
00:27:39,621 --> 00:27:42,891
Legally, there's no issue. I see.

456
00:27:43,551 --> 00:27:44,691
Yes, what a relief.

457
00:27:45,791 --> 00:27:48,661
"However,
from a societal perspective,"

458
00:27:48,861 --> 00:27:51,461
"emotional aversion and..."

459
00:27:51,631 --> 00:27:54,871
"a high likelihood
of facing social stigma..."

460
00:27:56,471 --> 00:27:57,471
Darn it.

461
00:27:58,701 --> 00:28:00,471
Who cares what other people think?

462
00:28:00,811 --> 00:28:03,981
Right? What's really important?

463
00:28:10,551 --> 00:28:12,351
I'd understand if it was for work,

464
00:28:12,851 --> 00:28:15,121
but I said you must sleep at home.
Didn't I?

465
00:28:15,921 --> 00:28:18,021
I told you, I didn't mean to.

466
00:28:19,691 --> 00:28:23,091
Wanting to be with your loved one...
I get it.

467
00:28:23,191 --> 00:28:26,931
But you shouldn't cross some lines.
You're not married yet,

468
00:28:27,001 --> 00:28:28,601
and you live with your elders.

469
00:28:30,131 --> 00:28:33,401
When you act like this,
it might make the family...

470
00:28:33,501 --> 00:28:35,411
get the wrong impression
of your boyfriend.

471
00:28:35,911 --> 00:28:36,911
Right.

472
00:28:38,911 --> 00:28:42,151
But Grandma, about tomorrow...

473
00:28:42,211 --> 00:28:44,351
Does he really have to come
and meet everyone?

474
00:28:44,821 --> 00:28:47,591
Why?
Does Jun Hyeok not want to come?

475
00:28:48,351 --> 00:28:49,921
That's not it, but...

476
00:28:51,621 --> 00:28:54,061
If he does come,
please don't scold him too much.

477
00:28:54,861 --> 00:28:56,991
Scold him? Why would I do that?

478
00:28:57,601 --> 00:29:02,201
He lives all alone with no family.
I just want to make him a warm meal.

479
00:29:06,301 --> 00:29:07,941
Did your grandma give you
a hard time?

480
00:29:08,871 --> 00:29:10,171
No.

481
00:29:11,441 --> 00:29:13,341
Then why do you sound so down?

482
00:29:14,011 --> 00:29:18,551
Having to lie to my family,
I feel a little guilty.

483
00:29:18,921 --> 00:29:21,221
What can we do? What's done is done.

484
00:29:21,921 --> 00:29:25,161
Oh, I told Mr. Park to come
to my place tomorrow morning...

485
00:29:25,161 --> 00:29:26,291
so we can get our story straight.

486
00:29:27,061 --> 00:29:29,061
I'll head over early too.

487
00:29:29,331 --> 00:29:32,031
We need to make sure
Park Jun Hyeok doesn't slip up.

488
00:29:33,161 --> 00:29:36,531
- Good night, babe.
- "Good night, babe."

489
00:29:36,901 --> 00:29:38,001
Hey!

490
00:29:38,941 --> 00:29:40,941
Good going.

491
00:29:41,511 --> 00:29:42,871
You really think
you're fooling anyone?

492
00:29:43,311 --> 00:29:46,011
What's your plan here,
bringing Jun Hyeok home?

493
00:29:46,941 --> 00:29:50,351
He's my boyfriend.

494
00:29:51,051 --> 00:29:53,851
Come on. You can't fool me.

495
00:29:54,291 --> 00:29:57,591
How many times have you told me?
You said he's just a friend, right?

496
00:29:57,761 --> 00:29:59,921
You said nothing would happen...

497
00:30:00,121 --> 00:30:01,931
even if you were
the last two on Earth.

498
00:30:02,661 --> 00:30:03,661
What's your price?

499
00:30:04,031 --> 00:30:06,161
What's your price
to keep your mouth shut tomorrow?

500
00:30:07,701 --> 00:30:10,841
I can't put a price on this.
This is too complicated.

501
00:30:11,241 --> 00:30:14,571
Is Hyun Bin really fine with this?
How can he just stand by and watch?

502
00:30:14,911 --> 00:30:18,441
What choice do we have?
Telling them now would cause chaos.

503
00:30:24,081 --> 00:30:26,121
Thank you. Bye.

504
00:30:27,491 --> 00:30:29,951
About Mr. Park Jun Hyeok.

505
00:30:30,191 --> 00:30:34,131
He's a talented designer,
and he seems so sweet and friendly.

506
00:30:34,731 --> 00:30:36,031
About Ju Ah.

507
00:30:36,291 --> 00:30:38,931
Should we take this chance
and push her to get married?

508
00:30:40,771 --> 00:30:44,071
- Gosh, Dr. Han, Ms. Na! Hello.
- My goodness.

509
00:30:44,341 --> 00:30:45,371
Hello.

510
00:30:45,741 --> 00:30:48,371
- Looks like you're out shopping.
- Yes.

511
00:30:48,441 --> 00:30:51,141
I'm just going to go buy some meat.

512
00:30:51,181 --> 00:30:54,511
- See you at Dong Suk's opening.
- Okay, see you then!

513
00:30:54,581 --> 00:30:55,581
Bye.

514
00:30:58,021 --> 00:31:01,321
Well... Everything's all right
at home, I hope?

515
00:31:02,291 --> 00:31:03,291
Of course.

516
00:31:03,821 --> 00:31:07,021
Speaking of which, Ju Ah's boyfriend
is coming over to meet the family.

517
00:31:07,091 --> 00:31:08,491
That's why I'm out shopping.

518
00:31:09,361 --> 00:31:12,231
My, things are moving so fast.

519
00:31:12,361 --> 00:31:14,131
Wow, I'm so jealous.

520
00:31:14,631 --> 00:31:16,431
Things will work out
for Director Yang, too.

521
00:31:16,701 --> 00:31:18,441
Try not to be so anxious.

522
00:31:18,741 --> 00:31:20,071
You're right.

523
00:31:21,141 --> 00:31:25,281
You know, inside Hyun Bin's pillow,

524
00:31:25,841 --> 00:31:27,281
I put a talisman in there.

525
00:31:28,781 --> 00:31:29,781
My gosh.

526
00:31:30,111 --> 00:31:32,351
- A talisman?
- Yes.

527
00:32:00,551 --> 00:32:03,651
- How did you get here together?
- We were just getting some gifts.

528
00:32:03,881 --> 00:32:06,751
Wow, so you two are
at the "sharing door code" stage?

529
00:32:07,251 --> 00:32:09,551
Wait, are you two
wearing matching outfits?

530
00:32:10,151 --> 00:32:12,261
We coordinated our outfits
beforehand.

531
00:32:12,521 --> 00:32:14,161
My, what's with all this stuff?

532
00:32:15,091 --> 00:32:17,261
This one's for her grandmother.
This is for her mother.

533
00:32:17,261 --> 00:32:20,731
And this is a ribeye gift set
for the whole family to share.

534
00:32:21,101 --> 00:32:23,301
I paid for everything,
so don't worry, babe.

535
00:32:24,201 --> 00:32:25,341
"Babe?"

536
00:32:25,671 --> 00:32:27,911
Gosh, so cheesy! I know
we're not at the office, but...

537
00:32:27,971 --> 00:32:29,341
could you please tone it down
in front of me?

538
00:32:29,341 --> 00:32:32,811
Why? You're going to be calling me
"babe" at my house anyway.

539
00:32:35,011 --> 00:32:39,581
No way. Just call him Jun Hyeok.
Just Jun Hyeok.

540
00:32:40,251 --> 00:32:41,251
Yes, sir.

541
00:32:45,521 --> 00:32:47,221
I wonder what they're going to ask.

542
00:32:47,661 --> 00:32:50,391
Okay, first, you need to explain
why I slept over at your place.

543
00:32:51,031 --> 00:32:52,101
Right.

544
00:32:52,461 --> 00:32:56,531
I was sick, so you came over
to care for me and fell asleep.

545
00:32:56,631 --> 00:32:57,641
That should work, right?

546
00:32:57,941 --> 00:33:01,771
Don't try to play the victim.
Just tell them what happened.

547
00:33:01,841 --> 00:33:02,941
Be sincere.

548
00:33:03,741 --> 00:33:05,041
Okay, message received.

549
00:33:05,181 --> 00:33:08,651
And I've come up with
a few practice questions for you.

550
00:33:09,681 --> 00:33:12,551
Isn't it usually stuff like,
"What do your parents do?"

551
00:33:12,581 --> 00:33:15,121
"Do you have any siblings?"
"Is your job stable?"

552
00:33:15,351 --> 00:33:18,461
Isn't that what they'll ask?
But I have no parents or siblings.

553
00:33:18,521 --> 00:33:20,361
And they already know
all about my job.

554
00:33:20,461 --> 00:33:23,391
No, they won't ask
such predictable questions.

555
00:33:23,861 --> 00:33:26,501
The first thing they'll want to know
is how much you like me.

556
00:33:28,531 --> 00:33:32,001
I have something prepared for that.
It was for my future girlfriend.

557
00:33:32,171 --> 00:33:34,711
Go on, let's hear it.
I'll give you my objective opinion.

558
00:33:38,381 --> 00:33:39,611
My dear Ju Ah...

559
00:33:40,441 --> 00:33:44,251
is the person
who thawed my frozen heart.

560
00:33:45,681 --> 00:33:48,421
I was so lonely,
with no family to lean on,

561
00:33:48,491 --> 00:33:53,021
but she filled every one of my days
with joy and excitement.

562
00:33:54,361 --> 00:33:57,501
Hey, I can't listen to this.
Let's just wing it and move on.

563
00:33:58,131 --> 00:34:00,401
All right, next up. Our love story.

564
00:34:01,131 --> 00:34:04,871
Let's just use our friendship story.
Back when I was an intern,

565
00:34:04,941 --> 00:34:07,371
remember how I fell for you
and begged you to be my friend?

566
00:34:07,511 --> 00:34:08,511
You fell for her?

567
00:34:09,971 --> 00:34:12,611
I was the first person Taehan hired
through their blind recruitment.

568
00:34:14,981 --> 00:34:17,921
- Here, drink up. Here.
- Thank you.

569
00:34:19,881 --> 00:34:23,151
Back then, seriously...
The other interns...

570
00:34:23,221 --> 00:34:26,091
said she was a med school grad
and that she wasn't a design major.

571
00:34:26,161 --> 00:34:30,161
They trash-talked her nonstop.
But she aced the off-season sales...

572
00:34:30,231 --> 00:34:31,931
and shut everyone up in an instant.

573
00:34:37,171 --> 00:34:38,171
Oh, man...

574
00:34:39,171 --> 00:34:41,111
Did you dump the whole sugar bowl
in here?

575
00:34:42,141 --> 00:34:43,141
Did you?

576
00:34:44,711 --> 00:34:47,211
Yes, I did. So what?

577
00:34:49,151 --> 00:34:51,951
Director, you're so blinded
by jealousy right now...

578
00:34:52,021 --> 00:34:54,821
that you can't even see
how much you need my help?

579
00:34:55,521 --> 00:34:58,321
Yes, that was childish of me.
I'm sorry.

580
00:35:00,121 --> 00:35:01,161
Goodness.

581
00:35:10,331 --> 00:35:13,471
I'll ask about his marriage plans
and plans for kids.

582
00:35:13,701 --> 00:35:15,171
Plans for sharing childcare duties.

583
00:35:15,871 --> 00:35:16,871
Childcare...

584
00:35:20,851 --> 00:35:21,851
Sorry about that.

585
00:35:31,221 --> 00:35:33,291
Make a plan and share...

586
00:35:36,931 --> 00:35:39,701
My gosh! You scared me.

587
00:35:40,201 --> 00:35:41,531
What are you doing? What was that?

588
00:35:41,931 --> 00:35:43,231
Nothing. It's nothing.

589
00:35:43,731 --> 00:35:46,171
- What are you doing, Uncle?
- Well...

590
00:35:46,901 --> 00:35:49,811
I was listing mandatory questions
for my future nephew-in-law.

591
00:35:52,011 --> 00:35:54,911
"Marriage plans, family planning,"

592
00:35:55,111 --> 00:35:57,251
"how you'll share childcare duties
after marriage."

593
00:35:58,451 --> 00:36:00,351
Hey, what is all this?

594
00:36:00,421 --> 00:36:03,751
Isn't asking this on a first meeting
a little too much?

595
00:36:03,891 --> 00:36:07,531
What do you mean, too much?
I'm preparing a full interrogation.

596
00:36:07,661 --> 00:36:09,391
I'm going to put him
through the wringer.

597
00:36:09,991 --> 00:36:11,731
Do you know what I went through
to raise Ju Ah?

598
00:36:12,331 --> 00:36:14,371
No, no way.

599
00:36:15,201 --> 00:36:17,371
After
"plans to share childcare duties..."

600
00:36:26,311 --> 00:36:28,511
You have to be out of there
in one hour, tops.

601
00:36:29,751 --> 00:36:33,651
Come on, an hour will fly by
once we start eating and talking.

602
00:36:34,421 --> 00:36:36,791
Fine, two hours.
That's my final offer.

603
00:36:38,491 --> 00:36:41,291
Why? Are you nervous
that I'll win over the elders?

604
00:36:42,091 --> 00:36:44,361
Since I'm so charming,
they might say,

605
00:36:44,361 --> 00:36:45,561
"We want him for a son-in-law."

606
00:36:45,631 --> 00:36:47,361
"You two should hurry up
and get married."

607
00:36:47,731 --> 00:36:48,731
You're scared, aren't you?

608
00:36:51,971 --> 00:36:55,411
Ju Ah, what if they're like that?
What are you going to say?

609
00:37:28,171 --> 00:37:29,911
- My goodness!
- Oh, my.

610
00:37:29,971 --> 00:37:30,981
You brought two of them?

611
00:37:31,511 --> 00:37:33,041
Thank you so much for inviting me.

612
00:37:33,711 --> 00:37:37,721
I told you to come empty-handed.
Thank you.

613
00:37:39,021 --> 00:37:42,151
Ju Ah has told me so much about you.
Pleasure to meet you, Jun Hyeok.

614
00:37:43,321 --> 00:37:48,031
I've enjoyed your kimchi often,
but it's our first formal meeting.

615
00:37:49,491 --> 00:37:50,591
And this...

616
00:37:50,861 --> 00:37:54,531
It's not much,
but I got this for the family.

617
00:37:54,601 --> 00:37:55,601
My goodness.

618
00:37:55,601 --> 00:37:58,471
Not much? Come on.
This is a ribeye set, Dad.

619
00:37:58,741 --> 00:38:03,041
- Ribeye! She says it's ribeye.
- Gosh, you shouldn't have.

620
00:38:03,671 --> 00:38:05,281
Please, have a seat.

621
00:38:05,341 --> 00:38:08,911
So, should we chat for a bit
before we eat?

622
00:38:09,211 --> 00:38:11,351
- Yes, sir.
- Okay, good. Have a seat.

623
00:38:22,891 --> 00:38:23,891
(Stepmother)

624
00:38:23,891 --> 00:38:25,231
What time
do you think you'll get here?

625
00:38:25,601 --> 00:38:27,671
We can still have lunch together,
right?

626
00:38:39,441 --> 00:38:40,681
- Oh, dear.
- Goodness.

627
00:38:40,741 --> 00:38:42,351
Please, make yourself comfortable.

628
00:38:42,981 --> 00:38:44,721
Before I could even introduce myself
properly,

629
00:38:44,981 --> 00:38:48,151
I worried you all and let you down.
I'm really sorry.

630
00:38:48,991 --> 00:38:51,061
You certainly should be sorry.

631
00:38:51,061 --> 00:38:53,721
- You should be groveling.
- Dae Han, please.

632
00:38:55,331 --> 00:38:59,831
I've given it a lot of thought.
I'll ensure it never happens again.

633
00:39:00,361 --> 00:39:04,171
What you're worried about
did not happen. Rest assured.

634
00:39:04,301 --> 00:39:06,771
Oh, dear. Actually...

635
00:39:06,901 --> 00:39:09,311
We didn't ask you to come here
because of that.

636
00:39:09,711 --> 00:39:14,281
Ju Ah adores you, so we were curious
to meet the man she likes so much.

637
00:39:14,651 --> 00:39:17,781
And we wanted to treat you to a meal
while we were at it.

638
00:39:19,451 --> 00:39:23,491
I see.
Ju Ah gets her kindness from you.

639
00:39:26,691 --> 00:39:30,861
He's smooth. Still, this Park kid is
formidable. We need to be careful.

640
00:39:37,971 --> 00:39:40,501
I made a whole lunch.

641
00:39:41,471 --> 00:39:43,511
Why did you want to meet out here?

642
00:39:44,541 --> 00:39:46,841
Dad and Grandfather are waiting.

643
00:39:46,841 --> 00:39:48,681
Say what you need,
and let's go home.

644
00:39:54,421 --> 00:39:57,191
But why the long face, son?

645
00:39:59,991 --> 00:40:03,491
Don't tell me...
Did Ms. Gong tell you she met me?

646
00:40:03,961 --> 00:40:05,301
Did she snitch to you?

647
00:40:09,201 --> 00:40:10,471
It's because of this.

648
00:40:12,741 --> 00:40:14,371
That's...

649
00:40:15,241 --> 00:40:17,341
- Hyun Bin, this is...
- What is this?

650
00:40:18,011 --> 00:40:19,041
Could it be...

651
00:40:19,581 --> 00:40:22,351
a talisman to make sure things
work out between the VP and me?

652
00:40:22,611 --> 00:40:23,611
What?

653
00:40:25,951 --> 00:40:27,021
Yes.

654
00:40:28,691 --> 00:40:29,691
I...

655
00:40:31,021 --> 00:40:34,161
made it clear that
we're nothing more than friends.

656
00:40:35,561 --> 00:40:38,331
Still, you never know.

657
00:40:38,401 --> 00:40:40,901
No. Stop interfering.

658
00:40:41,531 --> 00:40:44,331
Not just with my father's affairs,
but with mine as well.

659
00:40:45,741 --> 00:40:48,271
- Look, I was just trying to help...
- I'm being serious.

660
00:40:49,111 --> 00:40:51,111
I'm becoming more and more
disappointed in you.

661
00:40:53,511 --> 00:40:54,511
And...

662
00:40:55,711 --> 00:40:58,251
there's someone else
I want to marry.

663
00:41:01,351 --> 00:41:02,651
Here. Have some of this.

664
00:41:02,921 --> 00:41:06,261
A patient gave me this
special liquor ten years ago.

665
00:41:06,721 --> 00:41:10,231
I was saving it for the day
I met my future son-in-law.

666
00:41:10,291 --> 00:41:13,061
I've been saving this for this day,
you know?

667
00:41:14,101 --> 00:41:16,571
Please, you don't have to be formal,
Father.

668
00:41:16,701 --> 00:41:18,941
Should I just talk casually then?
All right.

669
00:41:19,101 --> 00:41:22,741
- Right, let's have a glass. Go on.
- Thank you.

670
00:41:26,841 --> 00:41:28,181
He can handle his liquor.

671
00:41:29,511 --> 00:41:30,981
You and our Ju Ah...

672
00:41:31,751 --> 00:41:32,851
Are you planning on marrying her?

673
00:41:33,521 --> 00:41:35,021
Gosh, Uncle.

674
00:41:35,391 --> 00:41:38,521
- Marriage? You just met him.
- What's wrong with that?

675
00:41:38,791 --> 00:41:42,231
I just want to know if it's serious.
What's wrong with asking?

676
00:41:43,131 --> 00:41:47,001
The moment I first saw Ju Ah,
I just knew.

677
00:41:47,301 --> 00:41:52,041
That she was the one I was meant
to start a new chapter with.

678
00:41:52,341 --> 00:41:55,371
A new chapter! A new chapter begins!

679
00:41:55,511 --> 00:41:57,311
Wow, he's got a way with words,
doesn't he, honey?

680
00:41:58,881 --> 00:42:02,381
You're in the honeymoon phase
and only see the good in each other,

681
00:42:02,711 --> 00:42:07,521
but true love means
embracing each other's flaws.

682
00:42:08,291 --> 00:42:11,121
I'll take that to heart, Doctor.
I mean, Mother.

683
00:42:12,661 --> 00:42:16,091
All right, everyone, let's eat!
Eat up. Dig in.

684
00:42:16,161 --> 00:42:18,131
- Yes. Thank you for the meal.
- Sure.

685
00:42:19,061 --> 00:42:22,331
Here. Are you up for another one?

686
00:42:22,601 --> 00:42:26,141
- Yes, allow me to pour you a glass.
- Really?

687
00:42:26,201 --> 00:42:27,201
Yes.

688
00:42:28,041 --> 00:42:29,041
Look at that.

689
00:42:30,111 --> 00:42:32,581
Honey, can you believe it?
Mom, this day is finally here.

690
00:42:35,251 --> 00:42:38,481
Gosh, it's been over two hours.
What's taking them so long?

691
00:42:54,301 --> 00:42:55,501
Have you been waiting long?

692
00:42:55,571 --> 00:42:58,441
No, not at all. I just got here.

693
00:42:59,001 --> 00:43:01,871
Come on, Director.
You're a terrible liar.

694
00:43:03,041 --> 00:43:04,111
Have you been drinking?

695
00:43:04,711 --> 00:43:06,511
Yes, I had a few celebratory drinks.

696
00:43:06,941 --> 00:43:09,551
What?
And what's all that you're holding?

697
00:43:10,011 --> 00:43:13,681
This? Her grandma packed food for me
when she heard I live alone.

698
00:43:15,151 --> 00:43:16,151
Jealous?

699
00:43:18,421 --> 00:43:19,561
You know,

700
00:43:20,261 --> 00:43:22,031
I'm so happy that it's you,
Director.

701
00:43:22,461 --> 00:43:26,631
- What's there to be happy about?
- Come on.

702
00:43:27,031 --> 00:43:30,101
I mean, I'm glad you're the one
dating Gong Ju Ah!

703
00:43:34,241 --> 00:43:35,711
Oh, man...

704
00:43:36,541 --> 00:43:40,341
- Take good care of Ju Ah!
- Hey, come on. What are you doing?

705
00:43:42,681 --> 00:43:44,581
I should get going.

706
00:43:45,351 --> 00:43:47,081
Where to? I'll give you a ride.

707
00:43:47,151 --> 00:43:50,221
No, it's okay. I'll grab a cab.
You two have a nice date.

708
00:43:50,691 --> 00:43:52,961
Where are you going?
You have nothing better to do.

709
00:43:54,061 --> 00:43:56,031
That's not true!
I have someone waiting for me too.

710
00:43:58,261 --> 00:43:59,331
All right, I'm off.

711
00:44:00,231 --> 00:44:01,671
- Bye!
- Bye.

712
00:44:01,731 --> 00:44:02,871
Hey, thanks for your help today.

713
00:44:03,201 --> 00:44:04,201
No problem!

714
00:44:06,701 --> 00:44:07,701
Oh, hey...

715
00:44:12,441 --> 00:44:16,911
Ta-da! Look! We have galbi, japchae,

716
00:44:17,011 --> 00:44:19,221
and seasoned aralia sprouts.

717
00:44:19,421 --> 00:44:22,191
Wow! It all looks so delicious.

718
00:44:22,721 --> 00:44:24,351
Really?
You're going to share this with me?

719
00:44:24,591 --> 00:44:27,221
Of course!
How could I eat all this by myself?

720
00:44:27,291 --> 00:44:29,531
Luckily, they packed two of each
for us.

721
00:44:29,761 --> 00:44:31,561
Thank you.

722
00:44:32,331 --> 00:44:34,131
So, how did your mission go?

723
00:44:36,601 --> 00:44:37,601
I nailed it, of course.

724
00:44:39,471 --> 00:44:42,911
I was actually really jealous
of Director Yang today.

725
00:44:43,441 --> 00:44:44,441
Jealous?

726
00:44:44,711 --> 00:44:46,011
I already knew, but...

727
00:44:46,681 --> 00:44:50,351
Ms. Gong's family is
just so warm and loving.

728
00:44:51,321 --> 00:44:55,351
I was so envious that he gets to be
part of a family like that.

729
00:44:55,991 --> 00:44:56,991
I'm glad to hear that.

730
00:44:57,421 --> 00:45:00,061
Pacu Nacho was such a loner
back in Argentina.

731
00:45:02,131 --> 00:45:03,161
You must be a little bummed, right?

732
00:45:03,491 --> 00:45:06,701
That your guy friend
has a girlfriend now.

733
00:45:08,231 --> 00:45:09,301
Yes, a little.

734
00:45:09,601 --> 00:45:11,701
He used to tell me
every little thing.

735
00:45:11,901 --> 00:45:16,541
Yes, me too.
She's my one and only best friend.

736
00:45:16,971 --> 00:45:18,281
But what can you do?

737
00:45:18,281 --> 00:45:20,681
Your best friend loves him.
Just root for them.

738
00:45:22,711 --> 00:45:23,981
By any chance...

739
00:45:25,351 --> 00:45:26,881
If you're okay with it,

740
00:45:27,721 --> 00:45:29,091
could I be your new guy friend?

741
00:45:30,291 --> 00:45:32,691
Really? I'm so in.

742
00:45:34,361 --> 00:45:37,161
Then how about I come hang out
at the hospital on the weekends?

743
00:45:37,431 --> 00:45:38,861
We can watch dating shows together.

744
00:45:39,401 --> 00:45:41,131
I'd love that!

745
00:45:41,131 --> 00:45:43,231
Have you seen season three
of "Singles in Inferno?"

746
00:45:43,431 --> 00:45:46,471
Of course, I have.
Which couple are you rooting for?

747
00:45:47,401 --> 00:45:49,211
I'm glad it went well, but...

748
00:45:50,671 --> 00:45:51,681
I can't help feeling
a little insecure.

749
00:45:53,411 --> 00:45:56,111
What if your family ends up liking
Mr. Park more than me?

750
00:45:56,811 --> 00:45:59,521
What's with you?
This isn't like you, Yang Hyun Bin.

751
00:46:01,421 --> 00:46:02,821
While I was waiting outside,

752
00:46:03,791 --> 00:46:05,221
that thought
just popped into my head.

753
00:46:06,091 --> 00:46:09,161
All right, my future son-in-law,
drink up.

754
00:46:09,531 --> 00:46:10,791
- Thank you.
- Yes.

755
00:46:11,501 --> 00:46:14,061
- Wow, there.
- Oh, my.

756
00:46:14,061 --> 00:46:16,101
- Let me pour you a drink, too.
- That's right.

757
00:46:16,201 --> 00:46:19,371
I wish I could have been there
instead of him.

758
00:46:19,971 --> 00:46:23,311
- Drink up, have some more.
- Wow, he can really drink.

759
00:46:23,511 --> 00:46:24,611
That's it.

760
00:46:25,141 --> 00:46:26,781
- I like him.
- He passes.

761
00:46:29,281 --> 00:46:30,781
If I had been the one to go,

762
00:46:31,281 --> 00:46:34,821
there was something
I really wanted to tell your family.

763
00:46:35,421 --> 00:46:38,021
How much I cherish and love you,

764
00:46:38,761 --> 00:46:40,991
and how I plan to make you happy.

765
00:46:43,131 --> 00:46:44,361
I was bummed, too.

766
00:46:45,261 --> 00:46:48,001
I wanted to brag about
how much my boyfriend loves me...

767
00:46:48,001 --> 00:46:49,931
and how perfect he is.

768
00:46:50,001 --> 00:46:51,331
I wanted to show you off.

769
00:46:53,041 --> 00:46:54,271
I love just hearing you say that.

770
00:46:55,441 --> 00:46:57,611
Did your talk with your mom go well?

771
00:46:58,241 --> 00:47:02,151
Yes. No more misunderstandings
about the VP.

772
00:47:02,551 --> 00:47:05,481
I made it clear to her
that I'm in love with someone else.

773
00:47:12,761 --> 00:47:16,231
There's someone else
I want to marry.

774
00:47:19,931 --> 00:47:21,161
Who in the world could it be?

775
00:47:21,871 --> 00:47:22,871
It can't be...

776
00:47:23,901 --> 00:47:25,241
It's not Ms. Gong, is it?

777
00:47:28,271 --> 00:47:32,141
- Honey, did Jun Hyeok leave?
- Yes. Where's Dad?

778
00:47:32,741 --> 00:47:35,311
He had too much infused liquor
and passed out.

779
00:47:37,351 --> 00:47:39,521
Mother,
what did you think of Jun Hyeok?

780
00:47:39,921 --> 00:47:44,651
I heard he grew up without parents,
so I worried he might be troubled.

781
00:47:45,321 --> 00:47:47,621
But he's so bright and easygoing.

782
00:47:49,391 --> 00:47:50,791
What did you think of
your future brother-in-law?

783
00:47:50,791 --> 00:47:51,801
What?

784
00:47:52,801 --> 00:47:54,561
Yes, he was fine, I guess.

785
00:47:55,071 --> 00:47:57,901
Mom, don't act all friendly
with Jun Hyeok at work.

786
00:47:58,201 --> 00:48:00,871
If people find out we're dating,
it'll complicate things at work.

787
00:48:01,611 --> 00:48:02,611
Honestly.

788
00:48:04,111 --> 00:48:05,141
Hey.

789
00:48:05,441 --> 00:48:07,681
- I'm heading out for a bit.
- Oh, my.

790
00:48:08,881 --> 00:48:11,721
He's going to see his girlfriend,
isn't he? Right?

791
00:48:12,251 --> 00:48:15,521
A girlfriend? Oh, my.
Does Dae Han have a girlfriend?

792
00:48:15,921 --> 00:48:16,921
Apparently so.

793
00:48:17,191 --> 00:48:20,621
He'll introduce her to us soon.
He just said he needed some time.

794
00:48:20,921 --> 00:48:22,991
That's such a relief.

795
00:48:23,231 --> 00:48:26,631
Meeting someone new and having
those good feelings again...

796
00:48:26,801 --> 00:48:28,971
will help him heal
from his past wounds much faster.

797
00:48:29,471 --> 00:48:30,471
I suppose so, right?

798
00:48:31,801 --> 00:48:34,441
Who could it be?
The one whose shampoo smelled good?

799
00:48:34,801 --> 00:48:35,811
Shampoo?

800
00:48:36,311 --> 00:48:37,311
You know something?

801
00:48:37,771 --> 00:48:41,551
No, just something Uncle said once
when he was drunk.

802
00:48:43,811 --> 00:48:45,351
Shampoo?

803
00:48:50,791 --> 00:48:54,561
Did you order popcorn and a cola?

804
00:48:58,331 --> 00:49:00,201
Why did you want to meet here?

805
00:49:00,461 --> 00:49:04,271
- Weren't we having a meeting?
- That was just an excuse.

806
00:49:04,631 --> 00:49:06,541
I just called you because
I wanted to see you.

807
00:49:07,471 --> 00:49:10,871
I can come up with a plan myself.
Don't you worry about a thing.

808
00:49:11,811 --> 00:49:12,841
What's this all about?

809
00:49:13,811 --> 00:49:15,711
Look, Dong Suk, I...

810
00:49:16,551 --> 00:49:20,781
I asked an AI, and it said that
even if our parents live together,

811
00:49:21,221 --> 00:49:23,491
there's nothing legally stopping us
from being a couple.

812
00:49:24,621 --> 00:49:26,191
That might be true legally,

813
00:49:26,921 --> 00:49:28,891
but it's still going to look weird
to everyone else.

814
00:49:30,091 --> 00:49:31,491
I know it's a lot.

815
00:49:31,931 --> 00:49:34,401
I know we have a tough road ahead.
But...

816
00:49:34,631 --> 00:49:37,131
no matter what challenges
we have to face,

817
00:49:39,871 --> 00:49:43,071
I'll never let go of your hand.
I'll see us through it all.

818
00:49:43,841 --> 00:49:46,881
I'll make sure our brothers make up.
You trust me, right?

819
00:49:52,251 --> 00:49:53,821
What if someone sees us?

820
00:49:53,881 --> 00:49:56,891
Who's going to see? Give it here.
See? Problem solved.

821
00:49:56,951 --> 00:50:01,421
We'll just use this to cover up.
See? This will work.

822
00:50:06,401 --> 00:50:08,901
Oh, you're here for a movie?

823
00:50:09,601 --> 00:50:13,471
Yes. I like to watch movies
by myself.

824
00:50:13,841 --> 00:50:15,341
And after you told me
you were on duty today.

825
00:50:16,471 --> 00:50:18,841
That's because...

826
00:50:19,341 --> 00:50:20,681
If you didn't want to,
you could have just said so.

827
00:50:20,941 --> 00:50:22,581
Why did you have to lie about it?

828
00:50:23,211 --> 00:50:24,411
Well, I...

829
00:50:25,121 --> 00:50:28,821
It wasn't because I didn't want to.
Something just came up.

830
00:50:29,391 --> 00:50:30,391
Right, sure.

831
00:50:35,291 --> 00:50:37,061
Wait, what's that?

832
00:50:40,231 --> 00:50:41,771
Here, open wide.

833
00:50:42,071 --> 00:50:43,671
- Here.
- Here.

834
00:50:45,941 --> 00:50:47,641
- Stop messing around.
- That's...

835
00:50:47,701 --> 00:50:50,071
My bad. Okay, here it comes.
Open wide!

836
00:50:53,681 --> 00:50:55,411
Hey, Dong Ik. Yes, it's me.

837
00:50:56,111 --> 00:50:57,281
Your brother, Dae Han.

838
00:50:58,251 --> 00:50:59,851
Hey, Dae Han.

839
00:51:00,821 --> 00:51:03,721
What's up?
Why are you calling so late?

840
00:51:04,821 --> 00:51:09,831
Hey, I have a great idea
for you and my brother to make up.

841
00:51:10,331 --> 00:51:11,961
An idea to make up with Jeong Han?

842
00:51:12,501 --> 00:51:13,501
You really have one?

843
00:51:13,961 --> 00:51:17,131
Are you serious?
Can I really get my hopes up?

844
00:51:17,671 --> 00:51:22,071
Of course! This is a friendship
you just got back after 30 years.

845
00:51:22,441 --> 00:51:24,111
We have to get it back on track.

846
00:51:24,611 --> 00:51:25,611
So what's the idea?

847
00:51:26,141 --> 00:51:27,781
If it can just get Jeong Han
to come around,

848
00:51:28,381 --> 00:51:29,381
I'll do anything.

849
00:51:35,151 --> 00:51:36,591
Ju Ah, sweetie, what are you up to?

850
00:51:36,991 --> 00:51:38,291
Just checking on Dad.

851
00:51:38,621 --> 00:51:41,061
Wow, you're really maturing now that
you're old enough to get married.

852
00:51:54,101 --> 00:51:58,171
What's all this?
Getting the royal treatment?

853
00:51:58,941 --> 00:52:02,681
Why? Trying to see
if I approve of your boyfriend?

854
00:52:03,381 --> 00:52:07,521
Just because. You still seem upset
about what happened with the Yangs.

855
00:52:08,521 --> 00:52:09,951
I am.

856
00:52:10,821 --> 00:52:11,821
Dad.

857
00:52:12,161 --> 00:52:13,161
Yes?

858
00:52:15,961 --> 00:52:16,961
What?

859
00:52:18,431 --> 00:52:19,431
It's just...

860
00:52:20,101 --> 00:52:23,471
Can't you just try to understand
and forgive them?

861
00:52:24,031 --> 00:52:27,041
Honestly, Dad, you were happy that
our families made up, weren't you?

862
00:52:27,771 --> 00:52:31,981
The ends don't justify the means.

863
00:52:33,081 --> 00:52:34,081
Right now, I...

864
00:52:34,741 --> 00:52:37,751
It feels like all those good moments
we had are tainted,

865
00:52:38,881 --> 00:52:39,951
and it's tearing me apart.

866
00:52:40,551 --> 00:52:43,591
That's why you should forgive them.
Because you're the one in pain.

867
00:52:44,951 --> 00:52:46,991
Mom once told me...

868
00:52:47,761 --> 00:52:50,561
that forgiveness is about
setting yourself free.

869
00:52:51,331 --> 00:52:54,801
It's a choice you make for yourself,
to let go of your anger.

870
00:52:56,531 --> 00:53:00,271
And it sounds like Director Yang
gave his parents an earful, too.

871
00:53:01,001 --> 00:53:02,971
At least their son
has his head on straight.

872
00:53:03,511 --> 00:53:04,511
That's a relief.

873
00:53:05,881 --> 00:53:06,911
Right?

874
00:53:11,751 --> 00:53:12,951
Honey, are you feeling all right?

875
00:53:14,821 --> 00:53:16,221
Is it because of what Hyun Bin said?

876
00:53:17,191 --> 00:53:18,421
You want me to go
teach him a lesson?

877
00:53:19,691 --> 00:53:20,691
No.

878
00:53:21,661 --> 00:53:22,761
Just let it go.

879
00:53:24,291 --> 00:53:26,931
Why did you put that talisman
in there anyway?

880
00:53:28,001 --> 00:53:30,131
I truly thought of him
as my own son,

881
00:53:30,931 --> 00:53:32,571
and I did my absolute best.

882
00:53:33,841 --> 00:53:35,571
I guess my best wasn't good enough.

883
00:53:36,041 --> 00:53:38,411
Not enough? What do you mean?
How could you have done more?

884
00:53:38,611 --> 00:53:41,281
Right? It's not like you've ever had
a child of your own.

885
00:53:41,611 --> 00:53:44,051
How could you be expected
to be the perfect mother?

886
00:53:45,421 --> 00:53:46,421
Se Ri.

887
00:53:47,121 --> 00:53:48,521
From now on, live for yourself.

888
00:53:49,421 --> 00:53:50,421
All right?

889
00:53:52,621 --> 00:53:53,621
Okay.

890
00:53:55,061 --> 00:53:57,061
(Damga Charcoal Grill)

891
00:54:00,001 --> 00:54:03,101
The fridge is stocked. I just need
to wipe down the tables now, right?

892
00:54:03,171 --> 00:54:06,771
Yes, spray and wipe with this.
It cuts through the grease better.

893
00:54:06,901 --> 00:54:08,071
Okay.

894
00:54:15,251 --> 00:54:16,381
So today's your last day?

895
00:54:16,781 --> 00:54:18,681
Yes. It's been fun.

896
00:54:19,181 --> 00:54:21,251
Now that I'm actually leaving,
I'm a little sad.

897
00:54:22,651 --> 00:54:24,251
So, does this mean
we won't see each other anymore?

898
00:54:24,591 --> 00:54:28,991
Come on.
It feels like we were meant to meet.

899
00:54:32,161 --> 00:54:33,431
Then, is it okay
if I call you sometime?

900
00:54:34,201 --> 00:54:37,331
I'm really grateful for your help.
Let me buy you a meal on payday.

901
00:54:37,701 --> 00:54:38,901
I'd love that.

902
00:54:52,421 --> 00:54:54,581
Everyone's asleep,
so you can greet them tomorrow.

903
00:54:54,851 --> 00:54:55,851
Sounds good.

904
00:54:56,151 --> 00:54:58,621
Here.
You can keep these princess pajamas.

905
00:54:58,821 --> 00:55:02,231
No, that's okay.
I have pajamas in my backpack.

906
00:55:02,591 --> 00:55:05,161
Please, take them.
I wanted us to match like sisters,

907
00:55:05,231 --> 00:55:06,931
so I bought another one
just like it.

908
00:55:07,931 --> 00:55:11,001
You're impossible. All right, fine.

909
00:55:11,701 --> 00:55:14,671
Don't worry about Ji Hu.
I'll do my best to teach him.

910
00:55:15,201 --> 00:55:19,341
Don't worry about the restaurant.
I'll work hard to fill your shoes.

911
00:55:20,581 --> 00:55:24,151
For your first day,
you were really good.

912
00:55:25,081 --> 00:55:26,081
Really?

913
00:55:27,681 --> 00:55:29,391
But I noticed something earlier.

914
00:55:29,991 --> 00:55:31,391
Earlier what?

915
00:55:32,591 --> 00:55:34,561
I think Woo Jae likes you.

916
00:55:35,021 --> 00:55:37,991
What? No way. That's ridiculous.
What are you talking about?

917
00:55:39,331 --> 00:55:42,371
Woo Jae has never smiled
at me like that.

918
00:55:43,831 --> 00:55:45,471
That can't be right.

919
00:55:45,871 --> 00:55:48,401
Come on. You think I don't know him?

920
00:55:48,501 --> 00:55:51,411
My gosh. I'm not going to lie,
I was so jealous.

921
00:55:52,641 --> 00:55:54,681
- You were?
- Yes.

922
00:55:55,351 --> 00:55:59,481
But I can't blame him.
You're cool and smart.

923
00:55:59,751 --> 00:56:02,991
And since you're both in med school,
you two must have a lot in common.

924
00:56:04,051 --> 00:56:05,091
But...

925
00:56:05,361 --> 00:56:08,861
I don't have those kinds of feelings
for Woo Jae at all.

926
00:56:10,591 --> 00:56:13,531
I guess he's got a one-sided crush,
just like me.

927
00:56:15,871 --> 00:56:17,171
How can you...

928
00:56:17,431 --> 00:56:19,571
be so open and honest
about something like that?

929
00:56:20,441 --> 00:56:23,611
Because I like you, and I don't
want to be weird or pout.

930
00:56:24,171 --> 00:56:25,381
Wait, is this all your stuff?

931
00:56:25,911 --> 00:56:28,041
Yes, this is all I need.

932
00:56:33,621 --> 00:56:35,851
That's the pendant
Woo Jae found for you.

933
00:56:36,351 --> 00:56:38,861
- The one with the baby photo?
- That's the one.

934
00:56:39,921 --> 00:56:44,291
Apparently, this was in my things
when I was adopted.

935
00:56:47,601 --> 00:56:51,801
Your birth mom would recognize you
if she saw this picture, right?

936
00:56:52,571 --> 00:56:54,301
Yes, I guess so.

937
00:56:59,281 --> 00:57:02,751
Please take good care of Ji Hu.
He's not confident in English.

938
00:57:02,981 --> 00:57:03,981
Okay.

939
00:57:04,251 --> 00:57:08,891
First, I'll focus on English books
to spark his interest,

940
00:57:09,051 --> 00:57:13,121
and I'll create a curriculum
to improve his writing and thinking.

941
00:57:14,191 --> 00:57:16,731
Wow, you sound like a real teacher.

942
00:57:17,061 --> 00:57:21,001
I know, right?
No wonder Ji Hu insisted on Min Seo.

943
00:57:21,661 --> 00:57:26,371
I need your residence card and visa,
and proof of your leave of absence.

944
00:57:27,371 --> 00:57:30,171
- Is all that really necessary?
- Why are you being so cold?

945
00:57:30,311 --> 00:57:32,411
We have to be thorough
with identity verification.

946
00:57:34,581 --> 00:57:35,711
What are you smiling about?

947
00:57:37,451 --> 00:57:39,551
I was just thinking about
the first time we met.

948
00:57:40,151 --> 00:57:42,351
I'll get all the necessary documents
ready for you.

949
00:57:42,991 --> 00:57:44,991
Let's sign the contract
as soon as the papers are ready.

950
00:57:45,291 --> 00:57:47,361
And we'll pay you the going rate.

951
00:57:48,521 --> 00:57:52,261
Outside of tutoring hours,
feel free to travel as you planned.

952
00:57:52,331 --> 00:57:55,301
You can eat with us,
and for things like toiletries...

953
00:57:55,901 --> 00:57:57,471
She can just share ours, right?

954
00:57:58,201 --> 00:58:02,241
Yes.
Is there anything else you need?

955
00:58:03,341 --> 00:58:04,341
Actually...

956
00:58:04,671 --> 00:58:08,141
Would it be okay if I stayed here
in the second-floor living room?

957
00:58:08,641 --> 00:58:12,251
Why?
I said you could stay in my room.

958
00:58:12,721 --> 00:58:15,021
It's a bit uncomfortable.

959
00:58:15,851 --> 00:58:18,991
Then how about we clean out
the storage room for her?

960
00:58:20,691 --> 00:58:24,191
- I guess we could do that.
- Storage room? Is she Cinderella?

961
00:58:24,261 --> 00:58:27,031
Eun Bin, it's okay.
I'm more comfortable with that.

962
00:58:28,331 --> 00:58:29,401
Thank you.

963
00:58:32,871 --> 00:58:36,541
A voluntary excuse...
A letter of commitment.

964
00:58:36,611 --> 00:58:38,671
That's it, write it like that...
My gosh!

965
00:58:39,281 --> 00:58:40,341
Hey, you scared me.

966
00:58:40,811 --> 00:58:42,311
Why are you staring like that?
It's creepy.

967
00:58:42,581 --> 00:58:44,181
What?
Is there something you want to say?

968
00:58:45,151 --> 00:58:47,081
No, I was just wondering
what you're up to.

969
00:58:47,421 --> 00:58:49,691
What? Oh, this...

970
00:58:50,191 --> 00:58:54,361
My brother and Dr. Yang
had a bit of a falling-out,

971
00:58:54,491 --> 00:58:56,391
so I'm trying to figure out a way
to get them to make up.

972
00:58:57,631 --> 00:59:00,901
I see. You should definitely
help them make up, then.

973
00:59:02,571 --> 00:59:05,201
Is there anything I can do to help?

974
00:59:07,301 --> 00:59:08,341
That'd be great. Thanks.

975
00:59:09,071 --> 00:59:11,041
All right! Let me see.

976
00:59:11,811 --> 00:59:12,881
This is what I've got so far.

977
00:59:13,841 --> 00:59:14,981
This is no good.

978
00:59:15,311 --> 00:59:16,951
- A letter of commitment.
- This isn't...

979
00:59:17,351 --> 00:59:18,711
- No, but...
- Your handwriting...

980
00:59:19,681 --> 00:59:21,481
(This list of disciplinary actions
acknowledges my past errors...)

981
00:59:22,351 --> 00:59:24,621
- What's this?
- Oh, this.

982
00:59:24,991 --> 00:59:26,821
Bucket asked me to give this to you.

983
00:59:28,021 --> 00:59:29,031
What is it?

984
00:59:29,331 --> 00:59:32,301
I'm not sure. It's some kind of...

985
00:59:32,601 --> 00:59:33,961
punishment list he made
to show he's sorry?

986
00:59:39,571 --> 00:59:43,211
He says from now on, he'll take care
of all the odd jobs at the market,

987
00:59:43,271 --> 00:59:45,641
clean the public restrooms,
and handle pest control.

988
00:59:46,181 --> 00:59:48,081
He says
he'll take care of all of it.

989
00:59:51,781 --> 00:59:53,281
Take a look at it later.

990
00:59:56,521 --> 01:00:00,361
Hey, and also, about Dr. Yang...

991
01:00:00,961 --> 01:00:03,661
Your joint consult patient
is coming in today.

992
01:00:04,131 --> 01:00:06,661
Hey. You're going, right?

993
01:00:13,171 --> 01:00:15,171
(Sunny Korean Medicine Clinic)

994
01:00:16,511 --> 01:00:18,041
Hey! Dong Ik!

995
01:00:18,811 --> 01:00:20,081
Dong Ik. Hey.

996
01:00:20,341 --> 01:00:22,611
- You scared me!
- Come on, hurry out here.

997
01:00:22,911 --> 01:00:24,781
My brother's here!
He's agreed to the consultation.

998
01:00:25,181 --> 01:00:26,581
- What?
- Yes.

999
01:00:34,261 --> 01:00:36,731
So, what do you think
is the problem?

1000
01:00:38,161 --> 01:00:39,631
It's liver qi stagnation.

1001
01:00:40,931 --> 01:00:42,101
What does that mean?

1002
01:00:42,631 --> 01:00:45,501
It means the liver's energy
is blocked and has stagnated.

1003
01:00:46,571 --> 01:00:48,441
If we unblock that energy...

1004
01:00:48,941 --> 01:00:51,041
and get it circulating
with treatment,

1005
01:00:52,041 --> 01:00:53,781
the indigestion should clear up too.

1006
01:00:55,541 --> 01:00:56,551
Okay.

1007
01:00:59,481 --> 01:01:00,851
Let's give it a try.

1008
01:01:03,121 --> 01:01:04,451
Thank you, sir.

1009
01:01:09,361 --> 01:01:10,661
You'll feel better soon.

1010
01:01:11,831 --> 01:01:12,831
Okay.

1011
01:01:16,531 --> 01:01:18,531
- Let's do this.
- Let's do this.

1012
01:01:19,071 --> 01:01:22,041
(Sunny Korean Medicine Clinic)

1013
01:01:24,711 --> 01:01:25,711
What are you waiting for?

1014
01:01:26,381 --> 01:01:27,411
Jeong Han...

1015
01:01:33,221 --> 01:01:34,351
Yes, Councilor Hwang.

1016
01:01:37,191 --> 01:01:39,191
Of course,
I haven't forgotten our appointment.

1017
01:01:39,461 --> 01:01:40,761
I'll see you in a bit.

1018
01:01:41,791 --> 01:01:45,061
Yes, I'll be coming by myself. Okay.

1019
01:01:47,001 --> 01:01:48,001
What was that about?

1020
01:01:51,601 --> 01:01:53,341
Welcome. Hello.

1021
01:01:53,971 --> 01:01:55,971
So, did you talk to your son
about it?

1022
01:01:57,141 --> 01:01:58,711
I did, but...

1023
01:01:59,311 --> 01:02:01,981
Apparently,
my son has a girlfriend now.

1024
01:02:04,051 --> 01:02:05,081
Good for him.

1025
01:02:05,681 --> 01:02:07,121
I guess my daughter was
a step too slow.

1026
01:02:08,351 --> 01:02:09,891
Thanks for thinking of him, though.

1027
01:02:10,821 --> 01:02:12,051
Is that why you're here?

1028
01:02:12,461 --> 01:02:13,461
No.

1029
01:02:14,321 --> 01:02:15,321
Actually...

1030
01:02:15,791 --> 01:02:17,931
I was wondering
if I'm being too nosy,

1031
01:02:18,991 --> 01:02:20,401
so I was a bit hesitant
to say anything.

1032
01:02:21,331 --> 01:02:23,501
- Yes?
- Ms. Na.

1033
01:02:23,801 --> 01:02:25,631
You know
I've got a sharp eye, right?

1034
01:02:26,941 --> 01:02:29,441
I do. Why?

1035
01:02:30,171 --> 01:02:32,111
You see, I...

1036
01:02:33,081 --> 01:02:34,911
I think I saw Dr. Gong.

1037
01:02:36,551 --> 01:02:38,611
- My eldest son?
- No.

1038
01:02:39,121 --> 01:02:40,451
Your husband.

1039
01:02:41,081 --> 01:02:44,251
Dr. Gong,
the one who left home 30 years ago.

1040
01:02:51,561 --> 01:02:53,831
I keep telling you
I can do this by myself.

1041
01:02:54,961 --> 01:02:57,131
It's going to be my room.
Of course, I should help.

1042
01:02:57,531 --> 01:02:59,941
I'm sorry to be so much trouble.

1043
01:03:00,441 --> 01:03:01,501
Not at all.

1044
01:03:02,101 --> 01:03:05,611
I'm going to have it re-wallpapered
and get you a desk and a bed,

1045
01:03:05,781 --> 01:03:07,511
so just wait a few more days, okay?

1046
01:03:07,841 --> 01:03:09,211
Okay, thank you so much.

1047
01:03:10,011 --> 01:03:11,251
Oh, by any chance...

1048
01:03:12,421 --> 01:03:15,221
This dresser...
Could I maybe use it?

1049
01:03:19,891 --> 01:03:22,121
- Hold on.
- Okay.

1050
01:03:35,001 --> 01:03:36,741
The clothes and things inside...

1051
01:03:37,111 --> 01:03:38,871
Would you mind
if I just left them in here?

1052
01:03:39,411 --> 01:03:42,181
No, I don't mind at all.
I don't have many clothes anyway.

1053
01:03:49,991 --> 01:03:51,321
My gosh, this is so cute.

1054
01:03:52,351 --> 01:03:53,361
What's this?

1055
01:03:54,121 --> 01:03:55,591
It's a picture of me
when I was a baby.

1056
01:03:57,161 --> 01:03:58,191
Can I see?

1057
01:03:58,461 --> 01:03:59,531
Sure.

1058
01:04:06,841 --> 01:04:07,841
Mom!

1059
01:04:08,571 --> 01:04:10,671
- Gosh, you scared me.
- Come out here, quick!

1060
01:04:10,671 --> 01:04:11,771
- Why?
- Hurry!

1061
01:04:11,841 --> 01:04:13,581
- What is it? What's wrong with her?
- Just a second.

1062
01:04:13,641 --> 01:04:14,641
Seriously, what's gotten into you?

1063
01:04:58,821 --> 01:05:01,791
(Recipe For Love)

1064
01:05:02,021 --> 01:05:03,931
Best friends can become lovers,
you know.

1065
01:05:04,191 --> 01:05:06,061
Yes, that's right. We're dating.

1066
01:05:07,461 --> 01:05:08,961
How did it go with Councilor Hwang?

1067
01:05:09,031 --> 01:05:12,171
- Stop spying on me, you jerk.
- His name...

1068
01:05:12,271 --> 01:05:13,271
Gong Gi Cheol.

1069
01:05:14,141 --> 01:05:16,771
Now that I'm going to meet him,
I'm getting cold feet.

1070
01:05:16,841 --> 01:05:20,081
"To my beloved endorphin."

1071
01:05:20,181 --> 01:05:22,811
I'll see you at the grand opening.
Why did you call me out here?

1072
01:05:22,881 --> 01:05:23,951
What, did you want to make out
or something?

1073
01:05:26,721 --> 01:05:30,021
- Is that your boyfriend? Hello.
- Run!

1074
01:05:30,471 --> 01:05:32,471
Dramaday.me
